title: Guy Cogeval, former president of the Musée d'Orsay, dies at 70
subhed: A free spirit and nonconformist, often impetuous, the passionate lover of the 19th century left his mark on the Parisian museum from 2008 to 2017 with bold exhibitions. He died on November 13 at the age of 70.

title: The fall of Andrew, the black sheep of Britain's royal family
subhed: Once Queen Elizabeth II's favorite son, Prince Andrew lost his title and privileges after years of excess and proven ties to Jeffrey Epstein, the American financier accused of sexual crimes. King Charles III's decision was seen as inevitable to protect the monarchy.
